# 99-review-pr-skill — manual PR review

Trigger this rule explicitly (e.g. ask Cursor "@99-review-pr-skill review
this PR") to run the same workflow as the Claude `/review-pr` slash command
in [.claude/commands/review-pr.md](mdc:.claude/commands/review-pr.md).

## Procedure

1. Run `gh pr view --json number,title,body,headRefName,baseRefName,isDraft`
   (or ask the user if `gh` isn't available). Capture title, body,
   baseRefName, and isDraft.
   - Determine whether the PR is AI-authored or substantially AI-edited.
   - If it is, confirm the title starts with `[AI-Assisted]`.
   - If it is, confirm the body contains an originating agent transcript
     URL from one of the accepted forms (matching the guard workflow):
     `https://claude.ai/chat/<id>`, `https://claude.ai/share/<id>`,
     `https://claude.ai/code/session_<id>`, `https://cursor.com/share/<id>`,
     `https://chatgpt.com/codex/<id>`, or `https://jules.google.com/task/<id>`.
     Flag the literal placeholder `<CLAUDE_CHAT_URL>` as a violation ONLY
     when `isDraft` is false. Drafts may keep the placeholder while the
     transcript is not ready yet.
   - If it is not, do not flag the absence of the title prefix or
     transcript URL.
2. List changed files via `git diff --name-only origin/${baseRefName}...HEAD`
   using the captured `baseRefName` (PRs may target release branches, not
   `main`). Fall back to `gh pr diff <number> --name-only` if the local
   ref is missing.
3. For every rule in [pr-rules/common.md](mdc:pr-rules/common.md), scan the
   diff for violations. Report each as
   `path:line — common.md rule N: <one-line summary>`.
4. If any `*.py` files OR `pyproject.toml` changed, repeat step 3 against
   [pr-rules/python.md](mdc:pr-rules/python.md) and
   [pr-rules/python.local.md](mdc:pr-rules/python.local.md).
5. Repeat step 3 against
   [pr-rules/service-html2md.md](mdc:pr-rules/service-html2md.md).
6. Run `scripts/check_agents_consistency.sh`. Embed its output verbatim
   in the report under "Baseline consistency".
7. Summarize: Green / Yellow / Red verdict + violation count by ruleset.

## Output

Markdown report only. Do not edit files. Do not run `gh pr` mutations.
